sequenceDiagram
    participant Operator as Operator (admin user)
    participant Manager as Tool manager
    participant Identity as Identity and persona resolution
    participant Queue as Proposal queue
    participant Registry as Tool registry
    participant Memory as Memory store
    participant FS as Filesystem

    Operator->>Manager: approve_tool(proposal_id)
    Manager->>Identity: assert_admin(user_id)
    Identity-->>Manager: role_ok
    Manager->>Registry: begin_immediate()
    Manager->>Queue: load_proposal_for_update(proposal_id)
    Queue-->>Manager: proposal(requirements, artifact, checksum)
    Manager->>FS: lock_tool(tool_name)
    Manager->>FS: write_staging(tool_name, bytes)
    Manager->>FS: verify_checksum(staging_path, checksum)
    Manager->>Registry: insert_or_update_active_tool(tool_name, checksum)
    Manager->>Memory: write_seed_memory(tool_name, usage)
    Manager->>Queue: mark_approved(proposal_id)
    Manager->>FS: atomic_rename(staging_path, active_path)
    Note over Manager,FS: Rename happens before commit so the active DB row never references a missing file.
    alt commit succeeds
      Manager->>Registry: commit()
      Manager->>FS: unlock_tool(tool_name)
      Manager-->>Operator: approval_result(tool_name, checksum)
    else step before commit or commit fails
      Manager->>Registry: rollback()
      Manager->>FS: remove_staging_or_final(tool_name, checksum)
      Manager->>FS: unlock_tool(tool_name)
      Manager-->>Operator: approval_failed(error)
    end
    Note over Registry,Queue: BEGIN IMMEDIATE spans registry, reviewed tool.md, seed memory, and proposal status writes.
    Note over Manager,FS: DB is source of truth. Crash leftovers are repaired by tool sync.
